{"type":"message","id":"8b49a6fe","parentId":"0f6c49c9","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:12:45.430Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive view. Let me analyze this configuration in detail and compare it with the Linux configuration.\n\nKey observations:\n\n1. **Version**: D:\\coam uses version 2026.3.28 (meta.lastTouchedVersion), last modified 2026-04-17T07:09:43.561Z - this is very recent (today!)\n\n2. **Model Configuration**:\n   - `agents.defaults.model.primary` = \"codingplan/minimax-m2.5\"\n   - This means by default, the Windows system is trying to use minimax-m2.5 via codingplan provider\n   - The codingplan provider uses: `https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1` with API key `J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE`\n\n3. **Problem**: The `codingplan` provider in D:\\coam's openclaw.json uses a different endpoint and API key compared to what we saw in the Linux config. In Linux config, we saw:\n   - `codingplan` provider with baseUrl `https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1` and API key `J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE`\n   - This is the same, so minimax-m2.5 via codingplan should work!\n\n4. **But the user is asking about minimax-m2.7, not m2.5!**\n   - The default model is minimax-m2.5, not M2.7\n   - M2.7 is configured in the agents/main/agent/models.json (which we read earlier), but that file wasn't loaded because:\n     - The openclaw.json doesn't have a model provider for minimax (it only has ollama, deepseek, codingplan)\n     - The agents.defaults.model.primary is \"codingplan/minimax-m2.5\"\n\n5. **The Linux system** has:\n   - auth-profiles.json with minimax:cn pointing to MINIMAX_API_KEY env var\n   - agents/main/agent/models.json with minimax provider configured\n   - This is a more complete setup for M2.7\n\n6. **D:\\coam system**:\n   - .env has placeholder MINIMAX_API_KEY\n   - openclaw.json doesn't even reference minimax M2.7 anywhere\n   - Only minimax-m2.5 via codingplan is configured\n\nThe real issue is that D:\\coam's openclaw.json is missing the minimax provider entirely. The user is asking about M2.7 but the Windows config only has M2.5 available, and that M2.5 configuration is incomplete since it's not in the providers list.","thinkingSignature":"f3893b4b680587cf8afd16bd85715183cfc98adace4df6d124e9e7a88fdaabb3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4n9v4pasirsk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /mnt/d/coam/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37594,"output":656,"cacheRead":20856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59106,"cost":{"input":0.011278199999999999,"output":0.0007871999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00125136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013316759999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776427951353,"responseId":"063156ac569241551cc66d064e76dbd1"}}
