{"type":"message","id":"dad59dad","parentId":"f681f62b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:13:02.409Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The D:\\coam auth-profiles.json does have the minimax:cn profile with the actual API key. Let me compare:\n\nD:\\coam\\auth-profiles.json:\n- minimax:cn key: `sk-cp-TVuvlmq_fUfdvSwhbwPgAxgFoBCtPc1acKznw8MU2HeWtkWozK3ruBwFLNV2YKdlaYI5BCuiqQnWaI_kB6rmyrYw37SYXtIR1th4i71CR82WvLFT2kKZ_Ls`\n\nLinux ~/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json:\n- minimax:cn key: `sk-cp-TVuvlmq_fUfdvSwhbwPgAxgFoBCtPc1acKznw8MU2HeWtkWozK3ruBwFLNV2YKdlaYI5BCuiqQnWaI_kB6rmyrYw37SYXtIR1th4i71CR82WvLFT2kKZ_Ls`\n\nThey are the same! So D:\\coam does have the actual API key in auth-profiles.json.\n\nBut the issue might be in how the models.json is configured. Let me check if the minimax provider in D:\\coam's models.json is correctly set up.\n\nLooking at D:\\coam's models.json (which I already read), I saw:\n- minimax provider: baseUrl = \"https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic/v1\", apiKey = \"MINIMAX_API_KEY\"\n- minimax-cn provider: baseUrl = \"https://api.minimax.io/anthropic\", apiKey = \"MINIMAX_API_KEY\"\n\nBut the auth-profiles.json has the key for \"minimax:cn\" profile, not for \"minimax\" or \"minimax-cn\" provider directly.\n\n\nThe problem is that models.json is referencing MINIMAX_API_KEY as a string literal instead of pulling from the auth-profiles.json profile. Since the actual key lives in minimax:cn profile but the provider is looking for an environment variable named MINIMAX_API_KEY, there's a mismatch. I need to check if D:\\coam's .env file actually has this variable set or if it's missing entirely.","thinkingSignature":"674831b443fb1e3b44565b6459422d49fb7a3b981989d588b2b54efbe54dbca0"},{"type":"text","text":"D:\\coam 的 auth-profiles.json 里**已经有真实密钥**了！\n\n让我检查 models.json 中 API Key 的引用方式：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sy3x1zi5bli7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/d/coam/.op