{"type":"message","id":"7df804ba","parentId":"55f215ec","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:13:34.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Very interesting! The auth-state.json shows:- `minimax:cn` has `errorCount: 0` and `lastUsed: 1776351784135` - this is a recent timestamp (in milliseconds). Let me convert this:\n- 1776351784135 ms = Unix timestamp 1776351784 seconds\n- That's approximately April 2026 (current time is April 17, 2026)So minimax:cn was actually used successfully recently! And it has errorCount: 0, meaning no errors. The lastFailureAt is older (1776329668400), so there was a past failure but it recovered.But wait - the user is saying it's NOT working. Let me think about this more...\n\nActually wait - `lastUsed: 1776351784135` - let me check the current timestamp. Current time is April 17, 2026, about 20:12 GMT+8. \n\nLet me calculate: the current Unix timestamp should be around:\n- April 17, 2026 12:00 UTC ≈ 1744891200 seconds\n- 1776351784 seconds would be way in the future (like year 20256)Wait, that can't be right. Let me recalculate...\n\nActually Unix timestamps are in seconds, not milliseconds. But auth-state uses milliseconds:\n- 1776351784135 ms = 1776351784 seconds\n- From Jan 1, 1970 to April 2026: about 56 years = ~1760000000 seconds\n\nSo 1776351784 is plausible for April 2026.\n\nAnd the lastUsed timestamp for minimax:cn (1776351784135) is more recent than the lastFailureAt (1776329668400). This means minimax:cn was successfully used after a previous failure!\n\nSo minimax IS working on D:\\coam based on auth-state. \n\nThe user is saying it's not working though. Looking at openclaw.json, I see `agents.defaults.model.primary` is set to \"codingplan/minimax-m2.5\". The models mode is \"merge\", which means it combines providers from multiple sources. So the primary model being used is minimax-m2.5, not M2.7 - maybe the user is trying to use M2.7 specifically but the system is defaulting to M2.5 instead?\n\nThe key question is what \"not working\" actually means. Is it that M2.7 isn't available as an option at all, or that it's failing when invoked? Based on auth-state, minimax:cn has been successfully used, so the connection itself works. The issue might be that M2.7 isn't properly configured as the default model or isn't responding when called.","thinkingSignature":"7607d21e4c274946c659038c43cead51b3c1f4de95e3bcd38878dcc4c2aeb161"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ld4r817mcpk6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"stat /mnt/d/coam/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/models.json 2>/dev/null | grep Modify"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40915,"output":617,"cacheRead":20856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62388,"cost":{"input":0.012274499999999999,"output":0.0007404,"cacheRead":0.00125136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01426626}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776427996448,"responseId":"063156db11850d581595e1204668fead"}}
